archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: Addressing the Tech Services Architecture Threat Chain
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation:
This view shows at a high level the controls and requirements that may be put in place in order to address the Tech Services Architecture Threat Chain.
Such control implementations would need to be led by a highly skilled leader with the understanding of architecture methods and practices, and a passion and vision on how the architecture practice can be developed and improved over time and would require mandate.
Despite the risks being logged in the organization for quite some time, the current architecture leadership have not fully addressed these issues with sufficient quality or speed.
Following up on this a real architect may work with stakeholders to prioritize development based on business needs.
